  "prompt": "How can I find out when an Instagram was created?",
  "response": "To find out the creation date of an Instagram account, you can follow these steps:\n\n1. **Check the Profile Bio:** Sometimes, users mention the date they joined Instagram in their profile bio or display it in their posts.\n\n2. **Scroll to the First Post:** If the user hasn't deleted their early posts, scrolling down to the user's first post can give you an idea of when they started using Instagram. Keep in mind that the post date may not exactly match the account creation date if there was a gap between creating the account and posting.\n\n3. **Request Data from Instagram:**\n   - You can request data directly from Instagram, which will include the account creation date. \n   - Go to your profile, tap the three horizontal lines in the top right corner to access the menu.\n   - Tap \u201cSettings\u201d and then \u201cSecurity.\u201d\n   - Tap \u201cAccess Data\u201d under \u201cData and history.\u201d\n   - Scroll down to the \u201cAccount Information\u201d section. Here you can find the \u201cDate Joined\u201d information which tells you when the account was created.\n\n4. **Use Third-party Tools:** There are some third-party tools and websites that claim to provide information on account creation date, but using these might pose a risk to your account security and privacy. It's advisable to stick to methods provided directly by Instagram.\n\nRemember that this information might not be visible for accounts other than your own unless explicitly shared by the user.",
